reviewText: This is the best show on Adult Swim.  I can't wait to get this dvd so I can clear my DVR from past saved shows. Pick this up if you are ready for many laugh out loud moments and multiple viewings....For your health!Season 3 is now on and its as funny as the previous seasons!  Awesome job guys!

reviewText: Check It Out! With Dr. Steve Brule is a spinoff series of Channel Five Married News Team segments from both Tom Goes To The Mayor and Tim & Eric Awesome Show Great Job! that stars the bumbling physician Steven Brule in an early morning program showcasing things that he himself & hopefully the viewer want to find out about such as Relationships, Puppets, Food, etc. Think of it in the aspect of the those tapes that Mr. McFeely would show Mr. Rogers on occasion.The characterization of Brule as socially incompetent and ignorant man is BRILLIANTLY pulled off by veteran comedian actor, John C. Riley. One can't help but find humor in his genuine sincerity regarding the topics of choice and the people he interviews. He's like a little kid in a huge candy store that we call life and he just wants a heaping helping of whatever the heck god has in stock.While I may not personally care for Tim & Eric's other works, they somehow got it right with Check It Out!, probably because John C. Riley has far more input on it
summary: Early Morning Shlock Fer Yer Health

reviewText: Right off of the bat, don't buy this if you have never seen at least one episode of the show.  It isn't for everyone, as my wife will attest.  However, I love it and I know a bunch of hunks that are also huge fans of this show.  John C. Reilly is one of the top comedic actors out there right now and he plays this to the hilt.  Hilarious take of a public access show which usually finds Dr. Brule discussing a single topic for each episode.  Awesome!

reviewText: I bought this DVD as soon as it came out, and have been introducing Dr. Steve to people ever since. A few episodes is usually enough to get anyone to really like this show (besides my mom lol), anyone who finds alternative humor funny should definitely buy this. 6/5 stars for John C. Riley at his best.
